# ============================================================
# Portfolio Architect — .gitignore
# Generated 2026-05-25
#
# What lives in the repo: viewer + data + published pieces.
# What stays local-only: CV, audit/strategy docs, raw materials,
# history backups, OS metadata.
# ============================================================

# --- macOS / system noise --------------------------------------
.DS_Store
.AppleDouble
.LSOverride
._*
Thumbs.db

# --- Editor / IDE noise ----------------------------------------
.vscode/
.idea/
*.swp
*.swo
*~

# --- Private: CV (contains personal data — photo, phone, email)
cv/

# --- Private: application strategy ------------------------------
# Narrative, essay drafts, application-context (criteria/motivation/pushback).
# These are internal — the public site shows the work, not the strategy.
application/
application-context.json

# --- Private: raw source materials for each experience ----------
# Decks, screenshots, voice notes, source repos — often pre-launch / NDA.
# Only the FINISHED piece (under pieces/) goes public.
experiences/

# --- Private: local backups + deploy bundles --------------------
history/
exports/

# --- Backups of the portfolio itself ---------------------------
*.backup/
*.backup.*/

# --- Large media defaults (review before un-ignoring) ----------
# Uncomment if you want to keep media out of the repo by default.
# Hosting large videos on GitHub Pages eats bandwidth — better via
# YouTube/Vimeo embed or external CDN.
# *.mov
# *.mp4

# --- Node / dev artifacts (in case we add tooling later) -------
node_modules/
.env
.env.local
*.log
